mocca-edc
---------


Liverpool School of Tropical Medicine


http://www.isrctn.com/


See also https://github.com/clinicedc/edc



Installation
------------

To setup and run a test server locally

You'll need mysql. Create the database

.. code-block:: bash

  mysql -Bse 'create database mocca character set utf8;'


Create a virtualenv, clone the main repo and checkout master

.. code-block:: bash

  conda create -n edc python=3.8
  conda activate edc


Clone the main repo and checkout master

.. code-block:: bash

  mkdir ~/app
  cd app
  https://github.com/mocca-trial/mocca-edc.git
  cd ~/app/mocca-edc
  git checkout master


Copy the test environment file

.. code-block:: bash

  cd ~/app/mocca-edc
  git checkout master
  cp .env.tests .env


Edit the environment file (.env) to include your mysql password in the ``DATABASE_URL``.

.. code-block:: bash

  # look for and update this line
  DATABASE_URL=mysql://user:password@127.0.0.1:3306/inte


Continue with the installation

.. code-block:: bash

  cd ~/app/mocca-edc
  git checkout master
  pip install .
  pip install -U -r requirements
  python manage.py migrate
  python manage.py import_randomization_list
  python manage.py import_holidays


Create a user and start up `runserver`

.. code-block:: bash

  cd ~/app/mocca-edc
  git checkout master
  python manage.py createsuperuser
  python manage.py runserver


Login::

  localhost:8000



